Patient: How long should I walk each day?
Healthcare Educator: Start with 10 minutes a day. Gradually increase it to 30 minutes.

Patient: Can I do more intense exercises?
Healthcare Educator: Yes, but always start slow. Listen to your body and don't push too hard.

Patient: What about lifting weights?
Healthcare Educator: Light weights are fine. Avoid heavy ones as they can strain your heart.

Patient: Should I do any special exercises for my heart?
Healthcare Educator: Aerobic exercises like biking or swimming are good. They help strengthen your heart.